---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Contact | truckaccidentcalc.com';
const description = 'How to reach the editorial team at truckaccidentcalc.com — corrections, content suggestions, advertising questions, press.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Contact</h1>

  <p>truckaccidentcalc.com is a small editorial site run by The Click Lab. We read every message but do not provide legal advice and do not respond to case-specific intake by email. If you have an actual truck accident claim, the homepage includes an optional case-review form that connects you with attorneys &mdash; that's a disclosed advertisement, not this contact channel, and using it is always optional (see our <a href="/privacy/">privacy policy</a> for what's shared if you use it). This inbox itself doesn't process case intake or attorney matching.</p>

  <h2>What we respond to</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Corrections.</strong> If you spot a factual error &mdash; a regulation we got wrong, an outdated coverage minimum, a state-specific rule we mischaracterized &mdash; send us the page URL, the specific claim, and your source. We aim to acknowledge corrections within a few business days.</li>
    <li><strong>Content suggestions.</strong> If there's a topic in the truck accident space that you wish we covered (a specific FMCSA rule, a state-by-state comparison, a calculator feature), we'd like to hear it.</li>
    <li><strong>Advertising and partnerships.</strong> Our editorial content is monetized through Google AdSense only &mdash; we do not accept direct sponsorships or paid placements in guides or methodology. If you want to discuss editorial guest content that meets our independence standard, the answer is almost certainly no, but you can write. (Separately, the homepage's case-review form is a disclosed attorney-referral product &mdash; see "What we don't do" below and our <a href="/privacy/">privacy policy</a>.)</li>
    <li><strong>Press inquiries.</strong> We are happy to be cited in articles and educational materials. Reach out and we'll respond.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What this inbox doesn't do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Case intake by email.</strong> We are not attorneys. We do not provide legal advice. Please don't send us the facts of your case and ask what it's worth or who to sue &mdash; use the case-review form on the homepage if you want your situation evaluated by an attorney, or your state bar's lawyer referral service to find one directly.</li>
    <li><strong>Document review.</strong> Don't send settlement offers, medical records, police reports, or insurance correspondence for us to look at. Send those to your attorney.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>The homepage case-review form is the disclosed way this site connects readers with attorneys &mdash; see our <a href="/privacy/">privacy policy</a> for what's shared if you use it.</p>

  <h2>How to reach us</h2>
  <p>Email: <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a></p>
  <p>Subject line, please:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>[CORRECTION] page-url</code> for factual corrections</li>
    <li><code>[SUGGESTION] topic</code> for content suggestions</li>
    <li><code>[PRESS]</code> for media inquiries</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Mail to that address goes to the editorial team. We respond to most messages within 3&ndash;5 business days. We do not respond to AI-generated form letters, mass outreach for backlinks, or attorney lead-gen pitches.</p>

  <h2>Operating address</h2>
  <p>The Click Lab<br />
  Editorial correspondence, truckaccidentcalc.com<br />
  hey@theclicklab.agency</p>
</BaseLayout>
